com.betterit.kaligia.features

Class Sample

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.betterit.kaligia.features.Sample

  • public class Sample
extends java.lang.Object
    A Sample corresponds to one completed run, and hence can have multiple Run Segments within represented as Repeat objects
    See Also:
    Repeat

      • range

        public void range(java.lang.String[] ranges)
        Modify Sample Spectra such that Repeat's Wavenumber objects whose wavenumber property fall out side all of the given ranges are excluded
        Parameters:
        ranges - A single dimensional array of String, where each item is a String representation of an integer.
        The multiple ranges are formed from this single dimensional array like shown below: (letters represent integers as String)
        [A, B, C, D] ==> [ [A, B] , [C, D] ], here A-B and C-D would be the array of ranges
